@node "WhatIs" "What is MIDIMaestro?"
@{b}@{u}What is MIDIMaestro?@{ub}@{uu}

MIDIMaestro is a program designed to enable musicians to  convert  notes
played  on  an  instrument  into  @{"MIDI" link "MIDI" 0}  messages.  This  can  be done in
real-time or from a recording of the instrument as a file.
@endnode

@node "SystemRequirements" "System Requirements"
@{b}@{u}System Requirements:@{ub}@{uu}

MIDIMaestro requires any @{"Amiga" link "Amiga" 0} computer running OS  3.0  or  above.  For
real time  work  at least a 50 MHz 68030 processor with a 50 MHz FPU is
recommended. A sound sampler, connected to the parallel  port,  is  also
required  for  real  time  work  and  if  output is to be sent to a @{"MIDI" link "MIDI" 0}
interface then a @{"MIDI interface" link "MIDIInterface" 0} is also required.  To  work  from  sound
files a  @{"datatype" link "Datatype" 0}  will  have to be installed for the particular format
(datatypes for most common formats are a standard  part  of  Workbench). @{"MUI" link "MUI" 0}
3.0 or better is required for the user interface.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Instalation"
@{b}@{u}Installation:@{ub}@{uu}

Installation is very simple and is performed by the  standard  Commodore
Installer  utility.  Simply  double click on the Install icon and follow the
instructions.
@endnode

@node "Limitations" "Limitations"
@{b}@{u}Limitations:@{ub}@{uu}

Currently, MIDIMaestro only recognizes @{"NoteOn" link "NoteOn" 0} and @{"NoteOff" link "NoteOff" 0} messages. Only one
note may be played at a time.
@endnode

@node "FutureVersions" "Future Versions"
@{b}@{u}Future Versions:@{ub}@{uu}

I intend to develop MIDIMaestro to make it  more  reliable,  faster  and
have a  whole load of new features. The following features are hoped to be
implemented in future versions:

* Recognition of more @{"MIDI" link "MIDI" 0} messages (such as pitch bends).

* A piece of hardware to sample each string of a  guitar  seperately  so
  that chords can be recognized.

* Real time @{"spectrum analyzer" link "SpectrumAnalyzer" 0}.

* Real time @{"oscilloscope" link "Oscilloscope" 0}.

* Transcribing of music into standard music notation (with  support  for
  @{"tab" link "Tab" 0} on the guitar).

* Output to Amiga sound channels as well as @{"MIDI interface" link "MIDIInterface" 0}.

* Ability to select what instrument is to be used on which @{"channel" link "Channels" 0}  from
  within the program rather that on the @{"MIDI" link "MIDI" 0} equipment.

* Improved user interface.

* Improved documentation and on-line help.

* Fix some @{"known bugs" link "KnownBugs" 0}.

As can be seen I have a lot of work left to do to make this the ultimate
@{"MIDI" link "MIDI" 0} utility on the Amiga.
@endnode

@node "KnownBugs" "Known Bugs"
@{b}@{u}Known Bugs:@{ub}@{uu}

Sometimes if two notes are played in quick succession of each other  the
second note will not be identified.

The play and stop buttons on the input page don't do anything.

There are no instruments listed in the pop-up gadget for the  instrument
name on the output to file page.
@endnode

